SidecarScannerTemplate.name: US 52 Weeks IV Rank
SidecarScannerTemplate.description: A "dual sorted" scan, displaying the highest and lowest ranking implied volatility of the underlying US stocks within the recent 52 week period. IV Rank ranges from 0 to 100 where 0 rank indicates the current implied volatility is the lowest within the period and 100 indicates it is the highest within the period. IV Rank is calculated as ((Current IV - N-Week IV Low)/(N-Week IV High- N-Week IV Low))*100 where N is the number of weeks which is 52 for this scan.

SidecarScannerTemplate.name: US 52 Weeks IV Percentile
SidecarScannerTemplate.description: A "dual sorted" scan, displaying the underlying US stocks with the highest and lowest percentage of days with implied volatility closing below the current implied volatility over the recent 52 weeks. Percentile ranges from 0% to 100%. For example, if the last 4 days of daily implied volatility were 1.41%, 1.61%, 2.01%, 3.12% and the current is 1.91% then the latest is the 3rd highest out of 5 days or 60%.
